cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS

This paper deals with the use of activation functions in deep neural networks for tasks in vision, which is a common theme in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper specifically focuses on the use of Hermite polynomial expansions as a substitute for ReLUs, which is a technique that falls under the purview of machine learning and neural computing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.AI, followed by cs.NE and cs.DS.
